trans-unit.source: Stores objects that represent the static methods of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
The <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.LenientMathObject"></xref> class belongs to the built-in object model category.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.abs(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.acos(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.asin(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.atan(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.atan2(System.Double,System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.ceil(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.cos(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores a value that represents Euler's constant, the base of the natural logarithm, specified by the constant e.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.exp(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.floor(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores a value that represents the logarithm base e of 10, the natural logarithm of 10.
Stores a value that represents the logarithm base e of 2, the natural logarithm of 2.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.log(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores a value that represents the logarithm base 10 of e, the common logarithm of e.
Stores a value that represents the logarithm base 2 of e, the binary logarithm of e.

Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.max(System.Object,System.Object,System.Object[])"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.

Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.min(System.Object,System.Object,System.Object[])"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores a value that represents the ratio of the circumference of a circle to its diameter, specified by the constant π.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.pow(System.Double,System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.random"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.round(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.sin(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.sqrt(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
Stores a value that represents the following equivalent values: (√2)/2, √(½), and 1/(√2).
Stores a value that represents √2.
Stores an object that represents the static <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject.tan(System.Double)"></xref> method of the <xref href="Microsoft.JScript.MathObject"></xref> class.
